title.narrative: DIS(01)INCLUSIVE PROGRAMMES FOR CHILDREN WITH DISABILITIES

description.narrative: Inclusive programmes for children with disabilities UNICEF COs scale up evidence-based disability inclusive programmes in both development and humanitarian context, which contributes to Children With Disabilities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child an Equitable Chance in Life By 2021, UNICEF supported countries apply relevant policies, innovative approaches and evidence, to design and implement publicly and privately funded development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that give Every Child an Equitable Chance in Life

description.narrative: Through disability-inclusive development and humanitarian programmes, UNICEF reached over 4.8 million children with disabilities across 148 counties, double the number of children reached in 2020. Over half of UNICEF country offices with a Humanitarian Action for Children appeal – 36/66 or ;55 percent – systematically included children with disabilities in their response efforts in 2021.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/04/2021
